body: Of course it is, but you also have to have the right circumstances for it to pay off. Most of the time it doesn't, so if you know you're good enough you just have to keep trying and trying again until the opportunity does come. Out of *tons* of subreddits I've made, only about 2-4 of them could be called a success, and even then quite minor. There's no problem with that, they key is just persistence. But I was just wondering if you did anything different in particular to grow your guild so quickly.
